@page "/projects"

<h1 class="mx-auto text-center">Projects</h1>
<div class="content px-5">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-4">
            <div class="card">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h5 class="card-title">Final Year (University) project</h5>
                    <img src="../media/finalyearapp.png" class="card-img" alt="a picture of my final year application" />
                    <p class="card-text">A .NET Core MVC C# application that helps a Screwfix branch track training progress.</p>
                    <small class="card-text">Code withheld, but a demonstration is available on request.</small>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-4">
            <div class="card">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h5 class="card-title">An ApostropheCMS template</h5>
                    <img src="../media/Apostrophe.jpg" class="card-img" alt="apostrophe cms image" />
                    <p class="card-text">
                        This is an Apostrophe CMS Skeleton Kit that I released using Bootstrap 4. I figured it'd help someone starting out with the CMS,
                        which is useful for some bespoke projects. The community behind the CMS is quite small
                        and it isn't something you'd see in industry, but it's relatively simple to use
                        and could power basic sites.
                    </p>
                    <a href="https://github.com/patrickd77-eng/ApostropheCMSBootstrap4Skeleton" class="btn btn-primary">Repo</a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-4">
            <div class="card">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h5 class="card-title">A Python/Django blogging platform</h5>
                    <img src="../media/Blog.jpg" class="card-img" alt="A blogging platform" />
                    <p class="card-text">
                        This is a Bootstrap 4 blog template
                        that I released using the Django Framework.
                        Check it out! I figured it'd help someone starting out with django,
                        which is useful for quick projects using authentication.
                        Because this is a template repo with instructions,
                        it's very easy to be used or developed on. With some extra styling,
                        a fully functional CRUD capable blog could be made.
                    </p>
                    <a href="https://github.com/patrickd77-eng/DjangoBlogStarter" class="btn btn-primary">Repo</a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-4">
            <div class="card">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h5 class="card-title">A virus outbreak assessment tool</h5>
                    <img src="../media/virus.jpg" class="card-img" alt="a biological virus" />
                    <p class="card-text">
                        This is a very basic project featuring use of <a href="https://newsapi.org/">an API.</a>
                        The user is able to select a (biological) virus and see how "common" news articles
                        about said virus are at the moment.
                    </p>
                    <a href="https://github.com/patrickd77-eng/Outbreak" class="btn btn-primary">Repo</a>
                </div>
